<p>I have a fts3 table like this:</p>  <pre><code> CREATE VIRTUAL TABLE docs USING fts3(id, title, body); </code></pre>  <p>I want to make weight the matches in title higher than those in content like <a href="http://stackoverflow.com/questions/547542/how-can-i-manipulate-mysql-fulltext-search-relevance-to-make-one-field-more-val">this question</a></p>  <p>What I did:</p>  <pre><code>    SELECT               case when title match 'word' then 1 else 0 end as titleRank,             case when body match 'word' then 1 else 0 end as contentRank                 docs.*       FROM  docs       WHERE title match 'word' OR body match 'word'     ORDER BY titleRank desc, contentRank desc </code></pre>  <p>But seems the <code>select case</code> doesn't work with full text search (I use <a href="https://addons.mozilla.org/en-US/firefox/addon/sqlite-manager/" rel="nofollow">this tool</a>, there is no error, no response from this query, but if I remove <code>select case</code>, it works)</p>  <p>Where am I wrong? </p>